ng%20acumen%20plays%20incredibly%20on%20the%20small%20screen%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20might%20most%20recently%20remember%20Korean%20filmmaker%20Park%20Chan-wook%20for%20helming%20the%20excellent%202022%20film%20%26quot%3BDecision%20to%20Leave%2C%26quot%3B%20though%20he's%20had%20many%20other%20big-screen%20hits%2C%20including%20%26quot%3BOldboy%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BThe%20Handmaiden.%26quot%3B%20Park%20has%20directed%20television%20before%2C%20too%2C%20in%20the%202018%20series%20%26quot%3BThe%20Little%20Drummer%20Girl.%26quot%3B%20According%20to%20critics%2C%20his%20sensibilities%20on%20screen%20are%20part%20of%20what%20makes%20%26quot%3BThe%20Sympathizer%26quot%3B%20so%20rich.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPark%20has%20crafted%20a%20vibrant%2C%20faithful%20yet%20often%20audacious%20'Sympathizer%2C'%20premiering%20April%2014%2C%20that%20matches%20executive%20producer%20Nguyen's%20brilliant%20novel%20in%20both%20ambition%20and%20execution%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F6965283%2Fthe-sympathizer-review-hbo%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETime's%3C%2Fa%3E%20Judy%20Berman%20writes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pastemagazine.com%2Ftv%2Fhbo-max%2Fthe-sympathizer-review%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPaste's%3C%2Fa%3E%20review%2C%20written%20by%20Rory%20Doherty%2C%20lauds%20Park's%20direction.%20%26quot%3BHe%20navigates%20the%20precarious%2C%20panicked%20tension%20of%20Saigon's%20final%20days%20before%20falling%20to%20the%20North%20Vietnamese%20in%20the%20first%20episode%20with%20rhythm%20and%20purpose%2C%20and%20we're%20reminded%20how%20arresting%20characters%20can%20be%20under%20his%20watch%2C%26quot%3B%20Doherty%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInverse's%20Hoai-Tran%20Bui%20calls%20the%20miniseries%20%26quot%3Btwisty%2C%20stylish%2C%20and%20darkly%20thrilling%2C%26quot%3B%20praising%20it%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bjolt%20of%20electricity%20to%20a%20genre%20you%20didn't%20know%20needed%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221707%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22hoa%20xuande%2C%20fred%20nguyen%20khan%2C%20duy%20nguyen%20standing%20in%20a%20restaurant%20near%20a%20table%20with%20coffee.%20the%20man%20in%20the%20middle%20is%20wearing%20a%20military%20uniform%20and%20red%20beret%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66199aec1caec1275a6fd71f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHoa%20Xuande%2C%20Fred%20Nguyen%20Khan%2C%20and%20Duy%20Nguyen%20in%20%26quot%3BThe%20Sympathizer.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EHopper%20Stone%2FHBO%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20show%20balances%20multiple%20tones%2C%20landing%20somewhere%20in%20the%20dark%20comedy%20realm%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20sense%20of%20humor%20provides%20a%20welcome%20counterweight%20to%20the%20serious%20nature%20of%20the%20material%2C%20and%20also%20helps%20keep%20the%20fractured%20timeline%20clear%2C%20because%20the%20constant%20digressions%20and%20reversals%20are%20a%20running%20gag%20in%20and%20of%20themselves%2C%20worth%20paying%20attention%20to%20at%20all%20times%2C%26quot%3B%20Sepinwall%20writes%20for%20Rolling%20Stone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20an%20anti-war%20picture%20that%20underlines%20the%20moral%20rot%20of%20mass%20murder%20while%20reframing%20the%20Vietnam%20War%20from%20the%20historically%20suppressed%20perspective%20of%20the%20Vietnamese%3B%20it's%20a%20black-comic%20satire%20of%20white%20Americans'%20meager%20efforts%20toward%20inclusion%20and%20understanding%2C%20onscreen%20and%20off%3B%20it's%20a%20coming-of-age%20story%20of%20three%20friends%20whose%20personal%20loyalties%20are%20put%20to%20the%20test%20by%20political%20divisions%2C%26quot%3B%20IndieWire's%20Travers%20writes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20imbalance%20of%20the%20series%2C%20as%20it%20teeters%20between%20satire%20and%20thriller%2C%20personal%20drama%20and%20wry%20survey%20of%20cultural%20and%20political%20rot%2C%20seems%20deliberate%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vanityfair.com%2Fhollywood%2Fthe-sympathizer-hbo-series-review%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVanity%20Fair's%3C%2Fa%3E%20Richard%20Lawson%20writes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20critics%20weren't%20quite%20sold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20an%20overwhelming%20amount%20of%20plot%20jammed%20into%20'The%20Sympathizer%2C'%20and%20much%20of%20it%20operates%20in%20different%20tonal%20registers%2C%20lending%20the%20action%20a%20bumpiness%20that%2C%20however%20thematically%20apt%2C%20proves%20more%20wearisome%20than%20gripping%2C%26quot%3B%20Schager%20writes%20for%20The%20Daily%20Beast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221707%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22hoa%20xuande%20in%20the%20sympathizer%2C%20writing%20on%20a%20piece%20of%20paper%20on%20his%20dashboard%20while%20sitting%20in%20a%20car.%20there's%20a%20smiley%20face%20reflected%20on%20his%20windshield%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66199b343f923f7dab07a251%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHoa%20Xuande%20in%20%26quot%3BThe%20Sympathizer.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EHopper%20Stone%2FHBO%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESome%20critics%20longed%20for%20the%20prose%20of%20Viet%20Thanh%20Nguyen's%20novel%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20the%20show%20reaches%20its%20conclusion%2C%20one%20gets%20the%20sense%20that%20the%20story's%20epic%20heft%20is%20probably%20best%20felt%20in%20prose%20form.%20'The%20Sympathizer'%20is%20a%20tale%20of%20identity%20careening%20across%20history%20that%20may%20require%20more%20interior%20monologue%20than%20is%20generally%20permissible%20on%20television%2C%26quot%3B%20Vanity%20Fair's%20Lawson%20writes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCrucially%2C%20the%20series%20loses%20the%20heft%20of%20the%20book%2C%20sanding%20down%20its%20sharp%20edges.%20Elements%20of%20its%20mordant%20satire%20don't%20cut%20throu