22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Hackers%20from%20China%20and%20Russia%20are%20finding%20cracks%20in%20Microsoft's%20security%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225472%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Microsoft%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65fc5ec72417f97b87ce1b16%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223648%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Microsoft%20logo.%20%3Cp%3EDrew%20Angerer%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ERussian%20and%20Chinese%20hackers%20have%20been%20getting%20past%20Microsoft%20security.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIn%20the%20latest%20attacks%2C%20Russians%20compromised%20the%20emails%20of%20multiple%20federal%20agencies%2C%20watchdog%20group%20says.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAnother%20watchdog%20group%20published%20a%20report%20last%20week%20detailing%20Microsoft's%C2%A0%26quot%3Binadequate%26quot%3B%20security%20culture.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EChina%20and%20Russia%20keep%20finding%20ways%20to%20get%20past%20Microsoft's%20security%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cisa.gov%2Fnews-events%2Fdirectives%2Fed-24-02-mitigating-significant-risk-nation-state-compromise-microsoft-corporate-email-system%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20emergency%20directive%20made%20public%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Thursday%2C%20the%20US%20Cybersecurity%20and%20Infrastructure%20Security%20Agency%20(CISA)%20confirmed%20that%20Russian-backed%20hackers%20stole%20emails%20that%20had%20been%20sent%20between%20federal%20agencies%20and%20Microsoft%20%E2%80%94%20emails%20that%20may%20have%20contained%20users'%20login%20credentials.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECISA's%20directive%20requires%20the%20affected%20agencies%20to%20take%20immediate%20action%20to%20determine%20the%20extent%20of%20the%20breach.%20Specifically%2C%20they%20must%20analyze%20the%20stolen%20emails%20for%20signs%20that%20sensitive%20data%20or%20login%20information%20was%20leaked.%20The%20agencies%20whose%20logins%20were%20exposed%20have%20until%20April%2030%20to%20reset%20their%20passwords%20and%20authentication%20tokens.%20CISA%20did%20not%20specify%20which%20agencies%20were%20included%20in%20the%20breach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20hackers%2C%20a%20group%20known%20as%20Midnight%20Blizzard%20that's%20sponsored%20by%20the%20Russian%20state%2C%20first%20gained%20access%20to%20the%20Microsoft%20accounts%20in%20November%202023%20through%20a%20password-spraying%20attack%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmsrc.microsoft.com%2Fblog%2F2024%2F01%2Fmicrosoft-actions-following-attack-by-nation-state-actor-midnight-blizzard%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMicrosoft%20announced%20in%20a%20January%20press%20release%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20group%20increased%20their%20attacks%2010-fold%20in%20February%2C%20and%20by%20the%20following%20month%2C%20had%20accessed%20some%20of%20Microsoft's%20core%20software%20systems%2C%20the%20company%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmsrc.microsoft.com%2Fblog%2F2024%2F03%2Fupdate-on-microsoft-actions-following-attack-by-nation-state-actor-midnight-blizzard%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20in%20a%20March%20press%20release%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMidnight%20Blizzard's%20successful%C2%A0compromise%20of%20Microsoft%20corporate%20email%20accounts%20and%20the%20exfiltration%20of%20correspondence%20between%20agencies%20and%20Microsoft%20presents%20a%20grave%20and%20unacceptable%20risk%20to%20agencies%2C%26quot%3B%20CISA%20wrote%20in%20its%20emergency%20directive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20several%20years%2C%20the%20U.S.%20government%20has%20documented%20malicious%20cyber%20activity%20as%20a%20standard%20part%20of%20the%20Russian%20playbook%3B%20this%20latest%20compromise%20of%20Microsoft%20adds%20to%20their%20long%20list%2C%26quot%3B%20CISA%20Director%20Jen%20Easterly%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cisa.gov%2Fnews-events%2Fnews%2Fcisa-directs-federal-agencies-immediately-mitigate-significant-risk-russian-state-sponsored-cyber%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20a%20press%20release%20on%20Thursday%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BWe%20will%20continue%20efforts%20in%20collaboration%20with%20our%20federal%20government%20and%20private%20sector%20partners%20to%20protect%20and%20defend%20our%20systems%20from%20such%20threat%20activity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMicrosoft%20wrote%20in%20its%20January%20press%20release%20that%20the%20Midnight%20Blizzard%20attacks%20were%20%26quot%3Bnot%20the%20result%20of%20a%20vulnerability%20in%20Microsoft%20products%20or%20services.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20has%20been%20under%20fire%20recently%20for%20its%20security%20practices%2C%20which%20one%20government%20watchdog%20group%20says%20are%20%26quot%3Binadequate%26quot%3B%20and%20in%20need%20of%20an%20%26quot%3Boverhaul.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%20the%20US%20Department%20of%20Homeland%20Security%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cisa.gov%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2024-04%2FCSRB_Review_of_the_Summer_2023_MEO_Intrusion_Final_508c.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ereleased%20a%20report%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Cyber%20Safety%20Review%20Board%20(CSRB)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-security-issues-government-report-chinese-hacks-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edetailing%20a%20%26quot%3Bcascade%26quot%3B%20of%20%26quot%3Bavoidable%20errors%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20company's%20security%20systems.%20And%20those%20errors%2C%20which%20the%20CSRB%20attributed%20to%20Microsoft%20not%20adequately%20protecting%20its%20customers'%20sign-in%20keys%2C%20allowed%20a%20Chinese%20hacking%20group%20to%20access%20the%20emails%20of%20senior%20US%20officials%20last%20summer%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20reference%20to%20the%20Chinese%20hacking%20incident%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20Microsoft%20previously%20told%20Business%20Insider%20